Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wide wedges (peeling optional). Pop the
wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste},
season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread
out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Pickled Pepper ==

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

In a bowl for the dressing, mix together ¼ tsp @sugar{to taste},
@oil{1%tbsp}, and the @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}.

Season with salt and pepper, add the chopped pepper, stir together and set
aside.

== Korma Aioli ==

In a separate bowl, mix together the @aioli{1%sachet},
@korma curry paste{1%sachet}, and @honey{2%sachets}.

== Crispy Katsu Chicken ==

Lay @Irish chicken breast{320%g} out and put your hand on top. Cut from
thicker end to thin point until there's 2cm left (don't slice fully through).
Open it up like a book.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and packaging.

Beat @egg{1} in a #bowl{}. Add the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} to another bowl with
salt and pepper.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
> due to vacuum packing used to keep it fresh.

Season the chicken with salt and pepper.

Dip each breast first into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring
they're completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

Place a large pan over high heat, adding enough oil to completely coat the
bottom.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly—heat for
> 2-3 mins before adding the chicken.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry
until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes} total. Turn every
~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

In the final 5 mins of cooking time, add the @chorizo{100%g} to the wedges.

Toss together and bake until wedges are done.

Add three-quarters of the @baby gem{120%g} salad leaves to the bowl of
peppers and toss to coat in the dressing.

Pop the buns onto your plates and spread some korma aioli over each bun base
and lid.

Sandwich the fried chicken and the reserved salad leaves between the buns.

Serve your wedges and pepper salad alongside.

Use any remaining korma aioli for dipping.